Buy this photo Photo: Santiago Mejia - The Chronicle, Photo Illustration By Katie Dowd Image 11 of 11 10 of our favorite 'Peanuts' quotes on its 65th anniversary 1  /  11 Back to Gallery On Oct. 2, 1950, the Peanuts comic debuted in nine newspapers nationwide. When its run ended in 2000, over 17,000 strips had been published in 21 languages for 355 million people worldwide. 
Today marks the 65th anniversary of that first comic strip, featuring the lovable worrier Charlie Brown, his gang of friends and his loyal pup Snoopy.
The world was the creation of Charles Schulz, who lived in the Bay Area from 1958 until his death in 2000. His first studio was in Sebastopol, and he later moved to Santa Rosa. Today, the Charles M. Schulz Museum is located there .
It's an insurmountable task to choose the best Peanuts quotes of all time, but we picked 10 favorites in the gallery above. What's your favorite Peanuts quote?
